The Queen could have offered Meghan "the role of a lifetime" - leading the tour in Belize, Jamaica and The Bahamas - had the Duke and Duchess of Sussex remained as full-time working royals, according to commentator Tony Parsons. However, this "royal yacht has sailed" as Meghan and Harry are no longer working members of the Firm, a move dubbed as Megxit. He wrote in The Sun: "Imagining them doing a gruelling meet-and-greet all over the Commonwealth is just a crazy dream. But seeing William and Kate looking uncomfortable in the Caribbean was a reminder of the historic opportunity that has been lost forever." FOLLOW LIVE UPDATES ON THE ROYAL FAMILY BELOW...